# Game Data & Balance

## Structure

- Enemy types: single `ENEMY_TYPES` map — hp, speed, damage, xp, scale together.
- Upgrades: templates in `Awards.js`; application logic in `UpgradeSystem.js` only.
- Skills: `SkillTree.js` defines tree; costs via `getSkillUpgradeCost`.

## Tuning rules

- Document units in comments (`hpHits`, mult vs flat, per-second).
- Difficulty multipliers live in `settings.js` (`spawnMult`, `hpMult`) — don't duplicate tables per difficulty.
- Caps (`CRIT_CHANCE_CAP`) next to the stat they limit.

## UI preview

- `getUpgradePreview` must mirror combat application — one effect schema, two consumers.
- Changing an upgrade effect shape requires both preview and `applyUpgrade`.

## Migration

- Renaming IDs: alias in `SaveData` migration, never silent drop of player progress.
- New default quests/skills: merge with `DEFAULT_SAVE`, don't overwrite player lists blindly.
